`serial.send(someHandler,"hello world \r\n",15);` seems error prone, relying on programmer discipline to get the length right is not needed.

This is also possible `serial.send(someHandler,"hello world \r\n");` and it entails no run time cost. Just add this to http://developer.mbed.org/users/marcuschang/code/AsyncSerial/file/9127f9fae61f/AsyncSerial/AsyncSerial.h

```
template<int I>
inline void send(send_done_t handler, const char (&buffer)[I]){
    send(handler, buffer, I);   
}
```

